  "body": "Consider following contract:\r\n```solidity\r\ncontract Foo {\r\n    function test() external {\r\n        console.log(\"Hello from solidity\");\r\n        revert(\"I reverted\");\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nNow let's call it from test suite:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nit('Console log test', async () => {\r\n    console.log(\"Hello from JS\");\r\n    const Foo = artifacts.require('Foo');\r\n    const foo = await Foo.new();\r\n    await foo.test();\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nExpected output:\r\n\r\n```\r\n      Console log test\r\nHello from JS\r\nHello from solidity\r\n     Error: VM Exception while processing transaction: reverted with reason string 'I reverted'\r\n      at Foo.test (contracts/ConsoleTest.sol:16)\r\n      at TruffleContract.test (node_modules\\@nomiclabs\\truffle-contract\\lib\\execute.js:169:26)\r\n      at Context.<anonymous> (test\\ConsoleTest.js:205:27)\r\n      at processTicksAndRejections (node:internal/process/task_queues:96:5)\r\n```\r\n\r\nActual output:\r\n\r\n```\r\n      Console log test\r\nHello from JS\r\nHello from solidity\r\nHello from solidity\r\n     Error: VM Exception while processing transaction: reverted with reason string 'I reverted'\r\n      at Foo.test (contracts/ConsoleTest.sol:16)\r\n      at TruffleContract.test (node_modules\\@nomiclabs\\truffle-contract\\lib\\execute.js:169:26)\r\n      at Context.<anonymous> (test\\ConsoleTest.js:205:27)\r\n      at processTicksAndRejections (node:internal/process/task_queues:96:5)\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote that `Hello from solidity` string was printed twice.\r\n\r\nI suspect that hardhat revert processing may be causing printing this twice but this means that either this implementation or console.log itself should consider only actually printing to console once. \r\n\r\nThis becomes exceptionally cumbersome when you have dozens of log lines printed interspersed with JS logs that only get printed once - it's hard to tell when happens what. This is a very desirable behavior change. Hope you'll see it this way and have time to fix.",
