    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Hi @Pzixel, sorry for the very late response.\r\n\r\nWhat's happening here is that Truffle's contract abstraction, for some reason, makes an `eth_call` after a transaction reverts. Since `eth_call`s also produce `console.sol` outputs, you are seeing the output twice.\r\n\r\nI don't think there's much we can do. Maybe we could do some change in the `hardhat-truffle` plugin after #3224 is available. But for the time being I'm going to close this issue.",
